 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of colour information association with vertices of tessellated geometry.  
     It does not provide specifications associated with the use of colours.
     Colours are defined using RGB8 integer triples or RGBT8 integer quadruples. 
   </p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   <li>association of colour information with vertices of tessellated geometry;</li>
   <li>specification of colours using integer triples or quadruples.</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
   <li>association of colour information with any geometry elements which are not tessellated;</li>
   <li>the specification of semantics associated with the use of colours.</li>
 </outscope>

